<br>
Hand-out system has innate bias to selection criteria. (level, class, attendence, personality - you name it)<br>
<br>
What tends to happen is that if you got 4 warriors in guild level 60, 60, 57, 53.  RARE NO DROP case is where its most obvious. Rare no drop item drops one of level 60 wariors automatically gets it.  <br>
<br>
Loot in guild gets upgraded every few months - new expansions, guild gets stronger etc etc.  Problem is Lvl 60 warrior still gets priority to new loot while cannot pass on the old  no drop items down to lvl 53 one.  Herein is the bias to loot hand-out system.<br>
<br>
BUT it can work if people in charge of loot distribution realize this and use &quot;all get one before one gets two &quot; <br>
<br>
