<br>
Infusion was partially formed due to &quot;imbalances&quot; in the way drops were being awarded to a semi-raid guild.  The plate classes made out like bandits when we went to ToV, the leather/chain classes got very few drops.<br>
<br>
Boss mob loot is &quot;tank oriented&quot; with very few drops for some classes, and with obvious priorities to get better items in the hands of the warlords (to kill more boss mobs faster).<br>
<br>
A number of members wanted a loot point sytem put into place.  I was one of them due to the fact that monks get screwed short of North ToV/Luclin boss mobs.  <br>
<br>
The real benefit of the raid point system is not that I can get loot.  Just that I can have some determination if I want &quot;that loot&quot; vs &quot;this loot&quot; assuming it drops.<br>
<br>
Our system costs will be designed such that the &quot;cost&quot; of an item will be high enough that a winner will use up the raid value of many weeks per item.  Hence, there will be little of that &quot;I am always on top&quot; mentality as a single item might cost the equivalent of 15-20 raids.  When we only raid 4 times a week, nobody will be able to stay on top very long if they take some of the high end loot.<br>
<br>
The big benefit we (Infusion) feels they might get it less bias/loot arguements AND more participation from members to help us get the loot.<br>
<br>
Nothing like a carrot to encourage raiding.<br>
<br>
Ironfang <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchanteez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chanteez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 10:49:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8829.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.uniserve.com/~mischief/teezepic1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> actually</span><hr size=1> We have multiple level 60 warriors<br>
