 I have heard examples of where point system allowed a cleric to loot a item which was better suited to another class, but because the person from other class didnt have more points they lost out (cleric wanted it as a fun item), tho was serious upgrade for the other.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaatrexvg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AatrexVG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 11:29:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8829.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: actually</span><hr size=1> Actually, in Valorguard, Jippy has the most points for the next item that drops, he acquires points by being annoying and spamming the guild with nonsense, its the only way for him to get the phat lewt he deserves... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglobinshade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Globin Shade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1625<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 11:34:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8829.topic&index=51>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.crimsontempest.com/images/CrimsonTempest.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well CT has done both</span><hr size=1> When I left it was decided (Well before I left really) to move to a point system. Why? Because we where a raiding guild. All our players where in TOV armor with epic/epic equivenlants. That lets us start at a pretty even level and for XP group makes us reasonably effective. This was all done by officers awarding stuff.<br>
<br>
